    {
      "id": "35fa4c71b43b6056988d38a6d2826f8724163620",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-01 05:57:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6df298d75ff6599df1a7d5290825a50cbcb24a2e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-02 01:56:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt looks like the upstream code is at https://github.com/intel/isa-l and the most recent release is 2.29, so we should stick with a known tag.\n\nOne option that I've seen with other projects is to have this Git repo checked out as part of e.g. autogen.sh so that it is available for building immediately.  That would allow us to link the library directly into \"lfs mirror resync\" and llite.ko without depending on an external package.  I couldn't find any RPMs or even a .spec file for this library, so it doesn't seem like it is installed separately very often.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0eb6323c55b3d773c9ed7073172842e1d30802ef",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 683,
        "name": "jenkins",
        "email": "devops@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jenkins",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2020-04-18 01:45:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified+1\n\nBuild Successful \n\nhttps://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/73455/ : SUCCESS",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "610c028bc3c39519924cd42ac1476777f5566045",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
