        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2020-04-18 01:45:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBuild 73455 (patch #1) will not be tested because: it is marked forbuildonly",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "12a5d4a516050e14014489d3e2606b88e215da1e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-22 10:27:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt would be good if this automatically downloaded or git cloned a specific tag from the isa-l github repo.  Otherwise, it seems that EC would not be build for most systems.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3509f97a765409e6e266c420cbc4644ead8732eb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-22 15:59:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYou could make your life way easier by using PKG_CHECK_MODULES",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0b8a49753e0f56d9f19728cbb0fb7c42b9908cb6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-22 20:57:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI'd think that this patch should at least go before patch https://review.whamcloud.com/38062 \"ec: lfs tool to setup erasure-coding layout\" so that it doesn't report support for EC when that isn't available.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d99a77be4d39555fd9f58013d1847e31b29474ed",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-22 21:51:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> You could make your life way easier by using PKG_CHECK_MODULES\n\nJames, could you please elaborate?  Is that an RPM thing, autoconf, Git, something else?  AFAICS, there isn't an (S)RPM package for isa-l anywhere, maybe because it is mostly used \"under the covers\" rather than something that users install?\n\nThat means either we need to make our own RPM package(s), check it out from Git directly for the developers/builders (making this automatic would be good), or possibly include the relevant parts of the source directly into Lustre (I think there is a *lot* that we don't need).  \n\nThe latter would be easier from a usability POV, but would need ongoing maintenance.\n\nAs it is, I think all of the later patches are failing because this library is not on the builders, but the code is not conditional on its presence.  Even if that were fixed (and it should be), then none of the EC functionality would actually exist for testing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
